Package: riftchat
Version: __VERSION__
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.11), python3-venv, python3-pip, python3-dev, libffi-dev, libssl-dev, libusb-1.0-0, build-essential, curl
Recommends: i2pd
Maintainer: Rift Maintainers <ops@rift.pw>
Homepage: https://rift.pw
Description: RiftChat - Reticulum mesh messenger
 RiftChat is a Reticulum-native messenger that works without the internet.
 Messages travel over LoRa radio, BLE, WiFi-Direct, Ethernet, or the public
 internet - whichever Reticulum transports are available.
 .
 Wire-compatible with Sideband, NomadNet, and Reticulum MeshChat over LXMF.
 Memory for the Mesh.
 .
 This package is a Rift-branded fork of Reticulum MeshChat by Liam Cottle (MIT).
 The fork carries upstream's MIT license intact; Rift additions are also MIT.
 .
 Installs on both amd64 and arm64 (Architecture: all) - Python wheels for
 native dependencies are resolved per-architecture at install time via pip.
